# DRD (Valgrind race detector) suppressions for libhttpserver tests.
#
# DRD and Helgrind report differently-shaped warnings on identical code, so
# the same benign third-party race needs a drd:-tagged block here (e.g.
# drd:ConflictingAccess / drd:CondErr) distinct from its Helgrind:Race
# counterpart in valgrind-helgrind.supp.
#
# Only third-party benign races may be suppressed here, and only at the
# library boundary (libmicrohttpd worker-thread lifecycle, gnutls, glibc,
# libstdc++). Every entry must be narrow and per-symbol — name the
# third-party frame, never a `...` wildcard spanning libhttpserver's own
# symbols — and carry a comment with the upstream reason.
#
# Any race that DRD reports inside libhttpserver's own locking — the
# route-table shared_mutex, the hook bus, block_ip/unblock_ip — is a REAL
# race and MUST be fixed in source, never suppressed (DR-008, mirroring the
# tsan.supp rule).
#
# Ships with NO entries: suppressions are added only when a concrete
# third-party finding surfaces during CI-side triage on the Linux lane
# (Valgrind is Linux-only and cannot run on the darwin dev/CI runners).
